      "sha256": "2b27b8d6b19ae4753cb7af17d5e7b4fa8420ee96f4fb143460b2ea8d084b6ee2",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "In other words, is $G$ Ramsey size linear?\n\nThis problem is #33 in Ramsey Theory in the graphs problem collection."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "de1b7cd5c70b32aa44e2db7d067c36ea1341ab77d3cfd22d73222223f116a867",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $G$ be a graph such that $R(G,T_n)\\ll n$ for any tree $T_n$ on $n$ vertices and $R(G,K_n)\\ll n^2$. Is it true that, for any $H$ with $m$ edges and no isolated vertices,\\[R(G,H)\\ll m?\\]"
    }
  },
